reviews_data.review_text: Bring back the cruffin.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Emily,

Thank you so much for coming in today to ask about the cruffins we used to have. You can still get them at Virtuoso in Waxhaw, NC as they were definitely one of our FAVORITES. Unfortunately because they are no longer delivered to us and with increasing costs to get a week's worth of cruffins delivered, our cost to pick them up would require us to charge $9 per cruffin to break even and I doubt even you'd want to pay that much. Because of that, we'll continue to focus on our in house baked goods, which unfortunately we could never come close the quality of those cruffins. Unfortunately for most food service, this is a challenge that everyone is facing in reducing their menu items, so we'll continue to focus on importing and roasting good coffee, sourcing our own bakers, or staying local within York county to offset those costs. Thanks again.

reviews_data.review_text: Bring back the cruffin.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Emily,

Thank you so much for coming in today to ask about the cruffins we used to have. You can still get them at Virtuoso in Waxhaw, NC as they were definitely one of our FAVORITES. Unfortunately because they are no longer delivered to us and with increasing costs to get a week's worth of cruffins delivered, our cost to pick them up would require us to charge $9 per cruffin to break even and I doubt even you'd want to pay that much. Because of that, we'll continue to focus on our in house baked goods, which unfortunately we could never come close the quality of those cruffins. Unfortunately for most food service, this is a challenge that everyone is facing in reducing their menu items, so we'll continue to focus on importing and roasting good coffee, sourcing our own bakers, or staying local within York county to offset those costs. Thanks again.
